13 WHEREAS, Mother Willie Bell Beatles possesses the vast wisdom which only comes
14 through experience and the strength of character which is achieved through overcoming the
15 many challenges of life; and
16 WHEREAS, a kind and generous person, Mother Willie Bell Beatles brings joy and
17 happiness to her family and to the many friends and neighbors who have the great pleasure
18 of knowing her; and
19 WHEREAS, she has witnessed a dramatic change in the world over the course of her
20 lifetime, and we salute her contribution to its progress through her tireless efforts on behalf
21 of her community and extended family; and
22 WHEREAS, by the example Mother Willie Bell Beatles has made of her life, she makes this
23 world a better place in which to live, and it is only fitting and proper that she be appropriately
24 honored during this very special and memorable time.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 commend Mother Willie Bell Beatles for her unselfish, dedicated, and loving service to the
27 members of her family and community; congratulate her on the remarkable occasion of her
28 97th birthday; and extend their most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Mother Willie Bell
31 Beatles.
